er husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isabelle","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , now in frequent use in the English-speaking world."]},{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]},{"name":"Isobelle","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabel de Sandford was born about 1297, in Whitchurch, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Robert de Sanford."},"et":{"Abt 1297–":"umbes 1297–Surnud","1292–1347":"1292–1347","1317–Male":"1317–Surnud","1297–Female":"1297–Surnud","1347":"1347","Abt 1297":"umbes 1297","1297":"1297","1292":"1292","1317":"1317","Sanford, Whitchurch, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Whitchurch, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Whitchurch, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Whitchurch, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1297–":"noin 1297–Kuollut","1292–1347":"1292–1347","1317–Male":"1317–Kuollut","1297–Female":"1297–Kuollut","1347":"1347","Abt 1297":"noin 1297","1297":"1297","1292":"1292","1317":"1317","Sanford, Whitchurch, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Whitchurch, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Whitchurch, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Whitchurch, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1297–":"environ 1297–Décédé